  "title": "Plant parasitic nematodes in ICRISAT Chickpea Fields",
  "abstract": "In a survey of 5 fields of chickpeas in Andhra Pradesh, India, Helicotylenchus indicus, Helicotylenchus retusus, Heterodera cajani, Heterodera sp., Hoplolaimus seinhorsti, Pratylenchus sp., Rotylenchulus reniformis and Tylenchorhynchus sp. populations were highest in fields in which sorghum and various other crops had been grown during the past 5 years",
